  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps under ventricular assist device operating conditions. A CFD-based hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was evaluated at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were flagged as epistemic gaps. The assessment team concluded that the model meets minimum credibility thresholds for the intended low-risk regulatory submission pathway and accepted the package under the Minimal profile. No structured ContextOfUse record is attached; the intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-dataset-2023",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2022"
  ],
